      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MARTIN MAGIC (4) finished second last start over 2138m at Albion Park, beaten a head. Best recent result was a win at Marburg three starts ago. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run and has the talent to find the winners' list. WELEASE WODDEWICK (3) won two starts ago then things went amiss last start when he copped interference then broke and finished 6 metres away in fifth over 2138m at Albion Park. Has the benefit of a good draw this time. Finds a nice race and can make amends. I GOT CHILLS NZ (6) was unplaced two starts ago then things went wrong last start when he broke and finished 7 metres away in eighth over 2138m at Albion Park. This doesn't look as hard so he is capable of turning things around. ROSTOVA (1) cannot be left out after registering a sequence of three top-three finishes, the latest at this circuit a week ago. Include from the pegs.",
